{
  "stem": "14708.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "After that, everything went like a very, very fast film.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My father, who was in our city a city alderman, very active in the chamber of commerce and other public activities, as well as in the Jewish community-- he was among the first one who was arrested.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But this was just for a few days, until the Germans somehow accommodated themselves.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But on April 5, if I am not mistaken, 1944, there was already the order to wear the yellow stars.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So we all had to sew on--",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh yes, oh yes.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I had a raincoat, and on the raincoat my mother sewed on the yellow star.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] I will never forget.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Once I went on the street in this raincoat and with the star, and across me came one of my classmates, a Protestant girl-- blonde, blue-eyed, suntanned, in a white linen dress.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "She was a picture of health and youth and happiness.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Naturally, she didn't-- she didn't greet me, or neither did I her.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But I remember-- then I thought myself, we both are 19, and why should I feel like 100?",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I will never forget this picture.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You said, naturally, she didn't greet you.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There was--",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Oh, there was a great polarization.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We went to the same class, but there was absolutely no socializing together.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The Jews were together.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "My parents had only Jewish friends.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And it was no mixing.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "In the main street, in our street where-- in our town, in our city, where there was the what is called the [HUNGARIAN], you know, what is-- a promenade.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "One side was for the officers and the Christian community, and on the other side, the Jews promenaded.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] So it was very, very exactly separated.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That was after the Nazi occupation in March--",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
